Data simulations for two conponents models

library(mrgsolve)
library(rstan)
library(dplyr)
library(rjson)

#Create data sets

TVKA = 2.5
TVQ = 15
TVCL = 10
TVV2 = 35
TVV3 = 105

No residual noise data set

modelName <- "Pop2Cpt_noresnoise"
mod <- mread("pop_noresnoise", getwd()) 
Building pop_noresnoise ... done.
see(mod)

Model file:  pop_noresnoise.cpp 
$PROB
# Example population PK model

$PARAM TVKA = 2.0, TVQ = 15, TVCL = 10, TVV2 = 35, TVV3 = 105

$PARAM @covariates
WT = 70

$PKMODEL cmt="GUT CENT PERI", depot=TRUE

$SET end=240, delta=0.5

$MAIN
double CL = exp(log(TVCL) + 0.75*log(WT/70) + ECL);
double Q = exp(log(TVQ) + 0.75*log(WT/70) + ECQ);
double V2  = exp(log(TVV2)  +      log(WT/70) + EV2 );
double V3  = exp(log(TVV3)  +      log(WT/70) + EV3 );
double KA = exp(log(TVKA));

$OMEGA @labels ECL ECQ EV2 EV3 
0.3 0.1 0.1 0.4 

$SIGMA 0

$TABLE
capture IPRED = CENT/V3;
capture DV = IPRED*exp(EPS(1));

$CAPTURE CL Q V2 V3 KA ECL

  
param(mod)

 Model parameters (N=6):
nSub <- 15

data <- expand.ev(amt = 80 * 1000, addl = 14, ii = 12, WT = rnorm(nSub, 70, 15)) %>% 
  mutate(dose=amt) 

mod %>% 
  data_set(data)  %>%
  carry.out(cmt, amt, ii, addl, evid, ss, WT) %>%
  mrgsim(Req = "DV", end=20, delta=0.5, rescort = 3) %>% 
  plot(DV~time)


out <- mod %>% 
  data_set(data)  %>%
  carry.out(cmt, amt, ii, addl, evid, ss, WT) %>%
  mrgsim(Req = "DV", end=20, delta=0.5, rescort = 3) %>%
  as.data.frame

out <- out[!((out$evid == 0) & (out$DV == 0)),]
out
N <- nrow(out)
nt <-  20 / 0.5
iObs <- with(out, (1:nrow(out))[evid == 0])
nObs <- length(iObs)

xsub <- subset(out, !duplicated(ID))
nSubjects <- length(xsub$ID)
startID <- (1:nObs)[!duplicated(out$ID)] 
endID <- c(startID[-1] - 1, N)

nIIV <- 4

Convert to Stan

data <- with(out,
             list(N = N,
                  nt = nt,
                  nSubjects = nSubjects,
                  start = startID,
                  end = endID,
                  nObs = nObs,
                  iObs = iObs,
                  time = time,
                  cObs = DV[iObs],
                  amt =  amt,
                  cmt = cmt,
                  evid = evid,
                  ii = ii,
                  addl = addl,
                  ss = ss,
                  nIIV = nIIV,
                  weight = unique(WT))) 
#with(data, stan_rdump(ls(data), file = paste0(modelName,".data.R")))
jsonData <- toJSON(data)
write(jsonData, paste0(modelName, ".data", ".json"))

Initial estimates

init <- function()
  list(CL_pop = rnorm(1, TVCL, 0.1),
       Q_pop = rnorm(1, TVQ, 0.5),
       V1 = rnorm(1, TVV2, 0.5),
       V2_pop = rnorm(1, TVV3, 1),
       ka_pop = rnorm(1, TVKA, 0.01),
       sigma = runif(1, 0.001, 0.5),
       omega = runif(nIIV, 0, 0.5))

inits <- init()
#with(inits, stan_rdump(ls(inits), file = paste0(modelName,".init.R")))
jsonInits <- toJSON(inits)
write(jsonInits, paste0(modelName, ".init", ".json"))

  mutate(dose=amt, WT = runif(n(), 40, 100)) 

mod %>% 
  data_set(data)  %>%
  zero_re() %>%
  carry.out(cmt, amt, ii, addl, evid, ss, WT) %>%
  mrgsim(Req = "CL, Q, V2, V3", end=40, delta=0.5)

modelName <- "with_ode_simple"
mod <- mread("pop_with_ODE", getwd()) 
Building pop_with_ODE ... done.
see(mod)

Model file:  pop_with_ODE.cpp 
$PARAM CL = 10, Q = 15, VC = 35, VP = 105, KA = 2.0, WT = 70

$SET delta=0.1 // simulation grid

$CMT GUT CENT PERI 

$MAIN
// Individual PK parameters
double CLi = exp(log(CL) + 0.75*log(WT/70) + ETA(1));
double Qi = exp(log(Q) + 0.75*log(WT/70) + ETA(2));
double VCi = exp(log(VC) + log(WT/70) + ETA(3));
double VPi = exp(log(VP) + log(WT/70) + ETA(4));

// Reparametrization
double k10 = CLi / VCi;
double k12 = Qi / VCi;
double k21 = Qi / VPi;

$ODE 
dxdt_GUT = -KA * GUT;
dxdt_CENT = KA * GUT - (k10 + k12) * CENT + k21 * PERI;
dxdt_PERI = k12 * CENT - k21 * PERI;

$OMEGA name="IIV"
0.0625 0.0625 0.0625 0.0625 

$SIGMA 0.01 0.01

$TABLE
double CP = CENT/VCi;
double DV = CENT/VCi * exp(EPS(1));
double WEIGHT = WT;

$CAPTURE CP DV WEIGHT
